description:
Hi,
We are having a problem with a query not being executed properly in virtuoso 7.2.4. Our use case is the replacement of some properties on a URI. We want to change the last-modified and the status of a certain resource. The delete query has optional clauses in the 'where' part so that if the resource does not have one of these properties, the other property is still removed.
This query behaved fine in version 7.0.0, but now it does not delete the triples with trans:status as predicate if the target URI does not have a last-modified value.
Here is the query that we are running.
PREFIX hier: <http://mu.semte.ch/vocabularies/hierarchy/>
PREFIX account: <http://mu.semte.ch/vocabularies/account/>
PREFIX voc: <http://example/some-vocabulary/model#>
PREFIX skosxl: <http://www.w3.org/2008/05/skos-xl#>
PREFIX skos: <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#>
PREFIX foaf: <http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/>
PREFIX dcterms: <http://purl.org/dc/terms/>
PREFIX trans: <http://translation.example.com/vocab/>
PREFIX rm: <http://mu.semte.ch/vocabularies/logical-delete/>
PREFIX typedLiterals: <http://mu.semte.ch/vocabularies/typed-literals/>
PREFIX mu: <http://mu.semte.ch/vocabularies/core/>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX app: <http://mu.semte.ch/app/>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
DELETE {
  GRAPH <http://mu.semte.ch/application> {
    <http://translation.example.com/tasks/sk/04b52c04-0620-4558-8f89-e252de2963ff> trans:status ?gensym0.
    <http://translation.example.com/tasks/sk/04b52c04-0620-4558-8f89-e252de2963ff> voc:last-modified ?gensym1.
  }
} WHERE {
  GRAPH <http://mu.semte.ch/application> {
    OPTIONAL { <http://translation.example.com/tasks/sk/04b52c04-0620-4558-8f89-e252de2963ff> trans:status ?gensym0. }
    OPTIONAL { <http://translation.example.com/tasks/sk/04b52c04-0620-4558-8f89-e252de2963ff> voc:last-modified ?gensym1. }
  }
};
INSERT DATA
{
  GRAPH <http://mu.semte.ch/application> {
    <http://translation.example.com/tasks/sk/04b52c04-0620-4558-8f89-e252de2963ff> trans:status "translated".
    <http://translation.example.com/tasks/sk/04b52c04-0620-4558-8f89-e252de2963ff> voc:last-modified "2016-11-30T10:37:28.403Z".
  }
}

Of course, when the target URI has a last-modified value, the query runs without a problem and deletes both old values.
Strangely, a workaround is to include the INSERT clause directly into the query instead of doing two queries as above.
Best,
Karel
